-- BOJ Current-Account Balance May Reach Record 43.5 Trillion Yen
-- B y   H i d e n o r i   Y a m a n a k a
-- 2012-06-25T23:02:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/boj-current-account-balance-may-reach-record-43-5-trillion-yen.html
The  Bank of Japan (8301) ’s current-account
balance may climb to a record 43.5 trillion yen ($546 billion),
the central bank said in a statement today in Tokyo.  The BOJ projection shows that deposits would exceed the
previous record of 42.57 trillion yen set on March 24 last year
following Japan’s earthquake and tsunami. The central bank will
announce the final figure later today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hidenori Yamanaka in Tokyo at 
